pageTitle: UntypeO : Outdated Mods : World of Warcraft AddOns
textBeforeTable: Optional Files (2) Version 1.0: Initial release. Learned that WOWI likes *.zip files better. Fixed a logical bug in the /ut slash command. Now it actually works! Version 1.1: Added /utd Added /utr Fixed a bunch of typos in the code. Now you see why I needed this addon. I couldn't even spell it's name correctly! Version 1.2: TOC update for 3.2 Removed /utpurge - it was nothing but a disaster waiting to happen Version 1.3: Known Issues: There is a known issue with taint and /tar (/target). I am still working on this issue. Anyone with ideas on how to help, feel free to chime in! If you have any questions or comments, don't hesitate to contact me! Adds the given typo to the list of typos to repair automatically if it is not already in the list, and replaces any previous value that it was set to before if it was already in the list. usage: /ut <typo to replace> <correct replacement> /utr or /utreplace Remove the given typo from the filter of things to fix. Useful when you're as dumb as the author and try to add a filter that is already being automatically corrected.
